  Running the program is rather simple, you just tell it what sort of output 
  file you want and where to get the OUTPUT.APL. The command line options 
  are as follows:
  
  Usage: CIT2DOOR BBS_TYPE [OUTPUT.APL]
  
      BBS_TYPE   = QBBS to make a DORINFO1.DEF
                   WWIV to make a CHAIN.TXT
      OUTPUT.APL = Full path and filename of the OUTPUT.APL
                   Defaultys to OUTPUT.APL in curent path
  
  Here is an example, this is for the program Global War, a Risk clone. One
  of my favortes. :-)
  
     ÚÄ[ GWAR.BAT ]ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ¿
     ³  @echo off                      ³
     ³  cit2door WWIV                  ³
     ³  e:                             ³
     ³  cd \bgame\gwar                 ³
     ³  war /W d:\cit\aplic\chain.txt  ³
